METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 3 TEEN-AGERS ARRESTED IN 4 BUNGLED HOLDUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three teen-agers who allegedly bungled four South Bay holdups in less than two 
hours were arrested Tuesday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Potential victims foiled the robbery attempts by claiming they had no money and 
speeding away in their cars. 
</P>
<P>
"None of them are candidates for brain surgeons," Sgt. Wally Moore said. 
</P>
<P>
Victor Goldsmith, 18; Randy Rogers, 18, and a 15-year-old youth were booked for 
investigation of attempted robbery, Moore said. The three Hawthorne youths said 
they were gang members. 
</P>
<P>
The string of robbery attempts began Monday night in Hermosa Beach when the 
trio allegedly tried to rob a man returning from a store, investigators said. 
It ended at about 12:30 a.m. Tuesday, when police stopped a car that matched 
descriptions given by witnesses. 
</P>
