<HEADLINE>
<P>
THIEF CUTS PHONE LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A thief scaled at least two 18-foot utility poles to steal 200 feet of 
telephone cable, cutting service Tuesday to 650 homes near Escondido, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Bell officials offered a $5,000 reward for information that helps 
authorities find the culprit, who was probably interested in selling the copper 
wire for scrap metal. 
</P>
<P>
At least 650 customers in rural subdivisions near Old Castle Road and Leisure 
Lane north of Escondido were left without service as a result of the theft. 
Most were in the 749- and 751- prefixes. 
</P>
<P>
Service was expected to be restored by the end of the day. 
</P>
