FISH REPORT: LAKE PYRAMID STRIPERS BITING INSIDE MARINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fishermen at Lake Pyramid are finding it unnecessary to explore the picturesque 
coves and coastline as striped bass continue to feed on shad and small trout 
right inside the marina. 
</P>
<P>
Kent Morgan of Canyon Country caught a 29-pound striper just beyond the boat 
dock in the Los Angeles County reservoir. Bob Hanley of Westchester, fishing 
the same area, caught three stripers averaging between 12-15 pounds. 
</P>
