<P>
Sadako Ogata, 65, a Japanese professor of foreign relations with experience in 
the U.N. Children's Fund, has been nominated as U.N. high commissioner for 
refugees, diplomatic sources said today. 
</P>
<P>
She would replace Thorvald Stoltenberg, who recently resigned to become deputy 
prime minister of Norway. 
</P>
